
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-xu-isis-mpls-elc-02.txt'>
    <title>"Signaling Entropy Label Capability Using IS-IS", Xiaohu Xu, Sriganesh Kini, Siva Sivabalan, Clarence Filsfils, Stephane Litkowski</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-xu-isis-mpls-elc-02.txt</link>
    <description>Multi Protocol Label Switching (MPLS) has defined a mechanism to load balance traffic flows using Entropy Labels (EL).  An ingress LSR cannot insert ELs for packets going into a given tunnel unless an egress LSR has indicated that it can process ELs for that tunnel. This draft defines a mechanism to signal that capability using IS-IS. This mechanism is useful when the label advertisement is also done via IS-IS.</description>
    <dc:date>2015-04-20T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
